@prefix narr: <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_PrimaryActors> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_PrimaryActors> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#PrimaryActors> ;
    narr:childCount "6"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "38b164b31d8d57ffdf4cfaa2b5de750a70d683f4" ;
    narr:narration """The primary actor landscape for aswritten.ai remains split between high-leverage enterprise entry points and the acute pain of mid-market operations. The [Fortune 500 enterprise buyers](narr:Observation_PrimaryActors_1) represent the top-down budget source, with [architecture/standards teams](narr:Narrative_ArchitectureTeamsBeachhead) serving as the identified beachhead for organizational influence. Within these enterprise environments, specific roles have emerged as critical conduits: the [Chief Architect](narr:Actor_CustomerArchitect_TinkererRef) who facilitated initial onboarding, and an [engineering manager](narr:Observation_CustomerEngManagerBridgeRole) who now functions as a bridge for maintaining coherence between architectural decisions and implementation. Conversely, the [operations persona](narr:Position_OperationsICP) is framed as a high-value ICP due to their role in managing internal chaos. This operational bottleneck is not limited to large firms; observations of a [5-person practice](narr:Obs_EarlyProspectInboundBottleneck) confirm that the same inbound-inquiry pressure exists at significantly smaller scales, suggesting a universal pain point regardless of organizational size.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Actor_CustomerArchitect_TinkererRef> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ArchitectureTeamsBeachhead> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EarlyProspectInboundBottleneck> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_CustomerEngManagerBridgeRole> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_PrimaryActors_1> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_OperationsICP> ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Fortune 500 companies (Intuit, State Farm, Uber) are primary actors committing budgets to AI agent infrastructure." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_PrimaryActors_1> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "The acupuncturist that I'm trying to work with actually does have the same pattern of being someone that fields inbound, you know, customer service and sort of inquiry constantly about his expertise" ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EarlyProspectInboundBottleneck> ] ;
    narr:keyPhrase [ narr:text "Series A operations people have acute pain: fragmented context (Notion hodgepodge), high decision velocity, CEO chaos, already live in ChatGPT." ; narr:phraseSource <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Position_OperationsICP> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The tension between targeting high-budget Fortune 500 entities versus the recurring pain patterns in small, 5-person practices." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_PrimaryActors_1> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Obs_EarlyProspectInboundBottleneck> ] ;
    narr:variation [ narr:text "The shift from architecture teams as a strategic beachhead to the engineering manager as the tactical bridge for implementation." ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Narrative_ArchitectureTeamsBeachhead> ; narr:over <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Observation_CustomerEngManagerBridgeRole> ] ;
    narr:writer "google/gemini-3.1-flash-lite" .
}